The West Africa Gas Pipeline Authority (WAGPA), has appointed Mrs. Chafari Hanawa Kanya as its new Director-General. He took over from Mr. Debo Barandao from Togo whose tenure ended recently. As part of the implementation of the West Africa Gas Pipeline Project (WAGP Project), the State Parties (Benin, Ghana, Nigeria, Togo) established the West African Gas Pipeline Authority (WAGPA) by the WAGP Treaty signed in Dakar on January 31,2003. NSIA Insurance Promotes Industry Acceptance Okomu Oil Plc Generates N37bn In 2021 WAGPA is a Public Establishment of an international nature with legal personality and financial autonomy